{
  "text": "The presence of a fibrotic focus (FF) was evaluated [CITATION_1] . A FF is a scar-like area or areas replacing necrosis in the center of a carcinoma. We previously reported an interobserver concordance of 85% for the estimated relative FF size [CITATION_2] . When multiple fibrotic foci are present, only the largest one is taken into account.",
